<h3>Lycanthropic Morphing</h3>

<p>Werewolves can be in one of three forms: Human, Warg or Wolf. Morphing between Human and Warg form requires a <%= minor_action %> as does morphing between Warg and Wolf form. To morph directly between Human and Wolf form requires a <%= major_action %> or alternatively two <%= minor_action %>s.</p>

<h4>Human Form</h4>

<p>In Human form weapons can be wielded and all armour and clothing can be worn. While in Human Form <%= str %> is reduced by one die type. All languages can be spoken and understood.</p>

<h4>Warg Form</h4>

<p>In warg form no weapons can be carried nor armour worn. Totems carried in Human Form have their effect. Loose fitting clothes are still worn. All skills are at their nominal levels. Any skill performed that requires holding or grasping objects has its level reduced by half. Wolf-tongue can be spoken but Common and Divine cannot. All languages can be correctly heard.</p>

<h4>Wolf Form</h4>

In Wolf form the level of the skill <%= skill 'Sprint' %> is doubled but all magic skills are halved. While in Wolf Form <%= str %> is reduced by one die type. Any task that requires holding or grasping objects cannot be performed. Clothes are no longer worn. Totemâ€™s carried in Human Form have their effect but have a penalty of one die type. Wolf-tongue is the only language that can be spoken or understood.

<h4>Bear Form</h4>

<p>In Bear Form no weapons can be carried nor armour worn. Totems carried in Human Form have their effect. Loose fitting clothes are still worn. While in Bear Form <%= str %> is increased by one die type. Wolf-tongue can be spoken but Common and Divine cannot. All languages can be correctly heard.</p>
<p>Only Urgan Elite can transform into bear form.</p>

